: Selections from the Dakis Joannou Collection, New Museum, New York, USA, March 3 – June 6, 2010, curated by Jeff Koons. Catalogue.\r\nIbrido: Genetica delle forme d’arte, PAC – Padiglione d’Arte Contemporanea, Milan, Italy, March 13–31, 2010, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio and Francesco Garutti. Catalogue.\r\nHaVE A LoOk! Have a Look!, FormContent, London, UK, May 7 – July 11, 2010.\r\nAlpha Omega: Works from the Dakis Joannou Collection, DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece, June 16 – December 29, 2010, curated by Massimiliano Gioni and Dakis Joannou. Catalogue.\r\nBarbaric Freedom, Simon Lee Gallery, London, UK, July 9 – September 11, 2010, curated by Anne Pontegnie.\r\n10000 Lives, The 8th Gwangju Biennale, Gwangju, South Korea, September 3 – November 7, 2010, curated by Massimiliano Gioni. Catalogue.\r\nIl Museo Privato: La passione per l’arte contemporanea nelle collezioni bergamasche, GAMeC – Galleria d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, October 6, 2010 – February 14, 2011, curated by Giacinto di Pietrantonio and Maria Cristina Rodeschini. Catalogue.\r\nClub 21: Remaking the Scene, One Marylebone, London, UK, October 13–23, 2010, curated by Oxana Maleeva and Steve Piccolo.\r\nHareng Saur: Ensor en de hedendaagse kunst / Hareng Saur: Ensor and Contemporary Art, Museum voor Schone Kunsten &amp; S.M.A.K., Ghent, Belgium, October 31, 2010 – February 27, 2011, curated by Johan De Smet and Ronald Van de Sompel. Catalogue.\r\nPlus Ultra: Opere dalla Collezione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, MACRO Testaccio, Rome, Italy, December 17, 2010 – March 20, 2011, curated by Francesco Bonami. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2011</strong>\r\nEspíritu y espacio / Spirit and Space: Collección Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Sala de Arte Santander, Boadilla del Monte, Madrid, Spain, February 9 – May 15, 2011, curated by Francesco Bonami, organized by Fundación Banco Santander and Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo. Catalogue.\r\nLa collezione della Galleria Civica di Modena: Fotografie e disegni dalle Raccolte, Galleria civica di Modena, Modena, Italy, April 2 – July 17, 2011.\r\nSurreal versus Surrealismo en el arte contemporáneo, IVAM Institut Valencià d’Art Modern, Valencia, Spain, October 6 – January 8, 2011, curated by Gianni Mercurio and Demetrio Paparoni. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n2012\r\nPrint/Out: 20 Years in Prints, Museum of Modern Art, New York, USA, February 19 – May 14, 2012, curated by Christophe Cherix. Catalogue.\r\nGli artisti italiani della Collezione ACACIA / The Italian Artists of the ACACIA Collection, Palazzo nReale, Milan, Italy, April 12 – June 24, 2012, curated by Gemma De Angelis Testa and Giorgio Verzotti, Catalogue.\r\nThe Residue of Memory, Aspen Art Museum, Aspen, USA, May 11 – July 15, 2012, curated by Heidi Zuckerman. Brochure.\r\n\r\nThese Peanuts are Bullets, Family Business, New York, USA, July 10–14, 2012, organized by Le Dictateur. Catalogue.\r\nFuoriclasse: Vent’anni di arte italiana nei corsi di Alberto Garutti, GAM – Galleria d’Arte Moderna, Milan, October 7 – December 9, 2012, curated by Luca Cerizza. Catalogue.\r\nMarco Colombaioni: I quadri di Annibale, Museo di Storia Naturale, Milan, Italy, December 7, 2012 – January 13, 2013.\r\n\r\n<strong>2013</strong>\r\nGroße Gefühle: Von der Antike bis zur Gegenwart / Deep Feelings: From Antiquity to Now, Kunsthalle Krems, Krems, Austria, March 10 – June 30, 2013, curated by Brigitte Borchhardt-Birbaumer, Irene Calderoni, Sylvia Ferino-Pagden, and Hans-Peter Wipplinger. Catalogue.\r\nThe System of Objects: The Dakis Joannou Collection reloaded by Andreas Angelidakis, DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece, May 15 – November 30, 2013, curated by Andreas Angelidakis and Maria Cristina Didero. Catalogue.\r\nBestiario contemporaneo: Fra arte e scienze, gli artisti italiani della collezione ACACIA / A Contemporary Bestiary: Between Art and Science, Italian Artists of the ACACIA Collection, Museo di Storia Naturale, Venice, Italy, May 31 – October 24, 2013, curated by Gemma De Angelis Testa and Giorgio Verzotti. Catalogue.\r\nIl Palazzo Enciclopedico / The Encyclopedic Palace, 55a Esposizione Internazionale d’Arte La Biennale di Venezia, Venice, Italy, June 1 – November 24, 2013, curated by Massimiliano Gioni. Catalogue.\r\nCollection Sandretto Re Rebaudengo: Have you seen me before?, Whitechapel Gallery, London, UK, June 18 – September 8, 2013, curated by Achim Borchardt-Hume and Francesco Bonami. The exhibition is part of the series Think Twice: Twenty Years of Contemporary Art from Collection Sandretto Re Rebaudengo.\r\nOut of the Blue, Cortesi Gallery, Lugano, Switzerland, October 11 – December 20, 2013, curated by Alberto Salvadori. Catalogue.\r\nIntenzione manifesta: Il disegno in tutte le sue forme / Manifest Intention: Drawing in All Its Forms, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, October 11, 2013 – January 25, 2014, curated by Beatrice Merz and Marianna Vecellio. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2014</strong>\r\nRitratto dell’artista da giovane / Portrait of the Artist as a Young (Wo)Man, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, June 10 – September 21, 2014, curated by Marcella Beccaria. Brochure.\r\nPer formare una collezione #3, Madre – Museo d’arte contemporanea Donnaregina, Naples, Italy, October 11, 2014 – in progress, curated by Alessandro Rabottini and Eugenio Viola.\r\n\r\n<strong>2015</strong>\r\nFobofilia: Opere dalla Collezione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, February 12 – April 12, 2015, curated by Irene Calderoni.\r\nFuture Season Past, Lehmann Maupin, New York, USA, February 28 – April 18, 2015, curated by Manuel E. Gonzalez.\r\nLiberi Tutti! Arte e società in Italia 1989–2001, Museo Ettore Fico, Turin, Italy, July 9 – October 18, 2015, curated by Luca Beatrice, Andrea Busto, and Cristiana Perrella. Catalogue.\r\nSpin-Off: Muestra de la Colección Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Centro de Arte Contemporáneo de Quito, Montevideo y Luis Dàvila, Quito, Ecuador, August 1 – November 30, 2015.\r\nEnnesima: Una mostra di sette mostre sull’arte italiana / An Exhibition of Seven Exhibitions on Italian Art, Triennale di Milano, Milan, Italy, November 26, 2015 – March 6, 2016, curated by Vincenzo de Bellis. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2016</strong>\r\nExquisite Corpse, The Mistake Room, Los Angeles, USA, May 14 – July 2, 2016, curated by Niklas Svennung.\r\nMy Blueberry Night, Residenza Casarotto di Albegno, Albegno di Treviolo (Bergamo), Italy, May 16, 2016, curated by Antonio Grulli, organized by Club GAMeC.\r\nCurated by (?), Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, June 30 – October 16, 2016 Versus: La sfida dell’artista al suo modello in un secolo di fotografia e disegno, Galleria civica di Modena, Modena, Italy, September 16, 2016 – January 8, 2017, curated by Andrea Bruciati, Daniele De Luigi and Serena Goldoni. Catalogue.\r\nEther, Galerie Chantal Crousel, Paris, France, October 15 – November 19, 2016.\r\nA occhi chiusi, gli occhi sono straordinariamente aperti, XVI Quadriennale d’arte, Palazzo delle Esposizioni, Rome, Italy, October 13, 2016 – January 8, 2017, curated by Luca Lo Pinto. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>PROJECTS</h2>\r\n<strong>1999</strong>\r\nIn Camera Caritatis, Globale Positionen 10, Museum in Progress, Vienna, Austria, curated by Massimiliano Gioni. (Conceived for this project, the work was presented on a double page of the newspaper Der Standard, Vienna, December 27, 1999.)\r\n\r\n<strong>2002</strong>\r\nDaily News, New York’s Hometown Newspaper, project curated by Aleksandra Mir, New York, USA, September 11, 2002.\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\nThe Addiction, November 1–22, 2005, Gagosian Gallery, Berlin, curated by Anna-Catharina Gebbers. Presented in the context of the 4th Berlin Biennale, the exhibition brought together private collections of various artists, including some preserved sea animals from Cuoghi’s collection.\r\n\r\n<strong>2010</strong>\r\nKINDERAMA, project by Roberto Cuoghi, commissioned by the DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece. Developed during the exhibition A Guest + A Host = A Ghost, held at the DESTE Foundation in Athens from May 7 to December 31, 2009, it took the form of a 3D stereoscopic viewer loaded with photographs of children interacting with the exhibited works. KINDERAMA was presented during the exhibition Skin Fruit at the New Museum in New York, USA, from March 3 to June 6, 2010.\r\n\r\n<strong>2011</strong>\r\nSolid Void, Progetto Diogene, Turin, Italy, November, 7–13, 2011. Workshop curated by Roberto Cuoghi and Gian Antonio Gilli.\r\n\r\n<strong>2013</strong>\r\nArimortis, Museo del Novecento, Milan, Italy, April 5 – September 8, 2013, group exhibition curated by Roberto Cuoghi and Milovan Farronato, in collaboration with DOCVA Documentation Center for Visual Arts. Catalogue.\r\n\r\n<strong>2015</strong>\r\nAmetria, Benaki Museum, Pireos St., Athens, Greece, June 12 – October 11, 2015, curated by Nicoletta De Rosa, Polina Kosmadaki, Alessandro Pasini, Tomaso Piantini, and Yorgos Tzirtzilakis. Group exhibition based on an idea by Roberto Cuoghi, organized by the DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art in collaboration with the Benaki Museum.','Exhi & Bio','','publish','closed','closed','','exhi-bio','','','2018-10-17 00:53:43','2018-10-16 22:53:43','',0,'http://localhost/robertocuoghi/?page_id=744',0,'page','',0),(745,1,'2018-10-16 00:41:23','2018-10-15 22:41:23','','Exhi & Bio','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-revision-v1','','','2018-10-16 00:41:23','2018-10-15 22:41:23','',744,'http://localhost/robertocuoghi/744-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(746,1,'2018-10-16 00:41:49','2018-10-15 22:41:49','','Bibliography','','publish','closed','closed','','bibliography','','','2018-10-16 00:41:49','2018-10-15 22:41:49','',0,'http://localhost/robertocuoghi/?page_id=746',0,'page','',0),(747,1,'2018-10-16 00:41:49','2018