:56','2018-10-16 21:44:56','',2,'http://localhost/robertocuoghi/?p=760',0,'revision','',0),(761,1,'2018-10-17 00:51:44','2018-10-16 22:51:44','Roberto Cuoghi (Modena, 1973). Lives and works in Milan, Italy\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2>SOLO EXHIBITIONS</h2>\n<strong>1997</strong>\nRoberto Cuoghi / Alberta Pellacani, Spazio Aperto, GAM – Galleria d’Arte Moderna di Bologna, Bologna, Italy, December 19, 1997 – January 7, 1998, curated by Walter Guadagnini and Dede Auregli.\n\n<strong>2003</strong>\nRoberto Cuoghi: Foolish Things, Eldorado project room, GAMeC – Galleria d’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, February 9 – March 30, 2003, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio and Alessandro Rabottini.\nRoberto Cuoghi, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 29 – October 30, 2003.\n\n<strong>2005</strong>\nThe Wrong Gallery, New York, USA, March 7–30, 2005, curated by Maurizio Cattelan, Massimiliano Gioni, and Ali Subotnick.\n\n<strong>2006</strong>\nMei Gui, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 22 – October 4, 2006.\nMbube, objectif_exhibitions, Antwerp, Belgium, October 26 – November 25, 2006, curated by Tommy Simoens. Catalogue.\n\n<strong>2007</strong>\nRoberto Cuoghi: Mei Gui, Centre International d’Art et du Paysage de l’Île de Vassivière, Beaumont du Lac, France, January 17, 2007. Presented in the context of Un million et quarante-quatrième anniversaire de l’art / 1 000 044 candles for art, held on January 17 in various venues throughout France.\n\n<strong>2008</strong>\nŠuillakku, Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, May 6 – July 27, 2008, curated by M. Beccaria. Catalogue.\n[Traveled to ICA – Institute of Contemporary Arts, London, UK, October 14 – November 23, 2008.]\n\n<strong>2011</strong>\nRoberto Cuoghi, UCLA Hammer Museum, Los Angeles, USA, January 22 – May 15, 2011, curated by Ali Subotnick. Brochure.\n\n<strong>2012</strong>\nZOLOTO, Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, May 30 – July 13, 2012.\n\n<strong>2014</strong>\nRoberto Cuoghi: Šuillakku Corral, New Museum, New York, USA, April 30 – June 29, 2014, curated by Massimiliano Gioni and Margot Norton. Catalogue.\nDa iḍā e piṅgalā a iḍā e iḍā o piṅgalā e piṅgalā, Le Consortium, centre d’art, Dijon, France, October 17, 2014 – January 11, 2015. Catalogue.\n[Traveled to Aspen Art Museum, Aspen, USA, February 13 – May 31, 2015]\n\n<strong>2016</strong>\nPutiferio, DESTE Foundation Project Space, Slaughterhouse, Hydra, Greece, June 21 – September 30, 2016.\n\n<strong>2017</strong>\nRoberto Cuoghi: Perla Pollina, 1996–2016, Centre d’Art Contemporain Genève, Geneva, Switzerland, February 22 – April 30, 2017, curated by Andrea Bellini. Catalogue.\n[Traveling to Madre – Museo d’arte contemporanea Donnaregina, Naples, Italy, May 15 –\nSeptember 11, 2017]\nImitazione di Cristo; “Il Mondo Magico” (The Magical World), Italian Pavilion, 57° Biennale di Venezia, Venice, Italy, May 13 – November 26, curated by Cecilia Alemani. Catalogue.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2>GROUP EXHIBITIONS</h2>\n<strong>1996</strong>\nOrizzontale verticale: Giovani artisti modenesi, 1a edizione, Palazzo della Provincia, Modena, Italy, December 14, 1996 – January 25, 1997, curated by Roberto Daolio and Corrado Levi. Catalogue.\n\n<strong>1997</strong>\nMenotrenta: 2a selezione di giovani artisti, Spazio Laboratorio Hajech, Milan, Italy, February 11 – March 8, 1997, curated by Francesca Pensa and Francesco Tedeschi. Catalogue.\nLAB.12.2 - T.I.N.A. (there is no alternative), Viafarini, Milan, Italy, April 18 – May 2, 1997, curated by R. Daolio.\nConversazione in giardino, Orto Botanico, Ferrara, Italy, September 27 – October 19, 1997, curated by Gilberto Pellizzola. Catalogue.\nRaccolta del disegno contemporaneo: Nuove acquisizioni 1994–1997, Palazzina dei Giardini, Modena, Italy, November 30, 1997 – January 25, 1998, curated by Claudia Zanfi. Brochure.\nVisual Rave, La Società Umanitaria, Milan, Italy, December 12, 1997 – January 12, 1998, curated by Antonio d’Avossa and Centro Arte a Parte. Catalogue.\n\n<strong>1999</strong>\nFine, Studio Armin Linke, Milan, Italy, May 31 – June 18, 1999, curated by Lorenzo Silvan. Catalogue.\nGuarene Arte 99, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo per l’Arte, September 25 – November 7, 1999, Guarene d’Alba (Cuneo), Italy, selected by Emanuela De Cecco. Catalogue.\nIn Camera Caritatis, Globale Positionen 10, Museum in Progress, Vienna, Austria, curated by Massimiliano Gioni.\n\n<strong>2000</strong>\n3nds: Milano, Salara, Bologna, Italy, May 19 – June 13, 2000, curated by Alessandra Galasso and Gianfranco Maraniello. Catalogue.\nFuori Uso 2000. The Bridges: Art on the highway / Arte in autostrada, Lungo fiume sud, Pescara, Italy, July 2–19, 2000, curated by Helena Kontova, Emanuela De Cecco, Hou Hanru, and Andreas Schlaegel &amp; Angela Rosenberg. Catalogue.\nFai da te / The Amateur View, Sparwasser HQ, Berlin, Germany, December 8, 2000 – January, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza.\n\n<strong>2001</strong>\nPrimo piano: Su la testa! Opere e argomenti in scena, Palazzo delle Papesse Centro Arte Contemporanea, Siena, Italy, February 4–11, 2001, curated by Sergio Risaliti.\nMagic and Loss in Pandæmonium: Biennial of Moving Images 2001, The Lux Centre, London, UK, March 2 – April 8, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza and Cristiana Perrella. Catalogue.\n[The exhibition was also presented at Artistinvetrina, Fendissime, Rome, Italy, March 2–6, 2001, in collaboration with The British School at Rome; CAC Contemporary Art Centre, Vilnius, Lithuania, March 21 – April 15, 2001: Magic &amp; Loss: Video by young Italian artists, MAN – Museo d’Arte Provincia di Nuoro, Nuoro, Italy, April 6 – May 6, 2001: Magic and Loss: Contemporary Italian Video.]\nPlay &gt;, Openspace, Milan, Italy, March 28 – April 29, 2001, curated by Gigiotto del Vecchio. Catalogue.\nEspresso: Arte oggi in Italia, Manifattura Tabacchi, Florence, Italy, June 10 – July 20, 2001, curated by Luca Cerizza and Gianfranco Maraniello. The exhibition was part of Boom!, a program of five exhibitions curated by Sergio Risaliti.\nIl dono: Offerta, ospitalità, insidia / The Gift: Generous Offerings, Threatening Hospitality, Palazzo delle Papesse Centro Arte Contemporanea, Siena, Italy, June 2 – September 23, 2001, curated by Gianfranco Maraniello, Sergio Risaliti, and Antonio Somaini, organized by ICI – Independent Curators International. Catalogue.\n[Traveled to Centro Culturale Candiani, Mestre (Venice), Italy, October 14, 2001 – January 6, 2002; Scottsdale Museum of Contemporary Art, Scottsdale, USA, February 7 – May 5, 2002; Bronx Museum of the Arts, Bronx, USA, November 27, 2002 – March 2, 2003; Mary and Leigh Block Museum of Art, Northwestern University, Evanston, USA, April 4 – June 22, 2003; Art Gallery of Hamilton, Hamilton, Canada, August 9 – October 18, 2003.]\nVideorom in The 1st Valencia Biennial: Communication between the Arts, various venues, Valencia, Spain, June 13 – October 20, 2001, curated by Cristiana Perrella. Catalogue.\nThe End of All Things, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, from June 20, 2001.\nTirana Biennale 1: Escape, National Gallery and Chinese Pavilion, Tirana, Albania, September 15 – October 15, 2001, invited by Jens Hoffmann. Catalogue.\nIn fumo: Arte, fumetto, comunicazione / In fumo: Art, comics, communication, GAMeC – Galleria\nd’Arte Moderna e Contemporanea di Bergamo, Bergamo, Italy, September 27, 2001 – January 6,\n2002, curated by Giacinto Di Pietrantonio. Catalogue.\n\n<strong>2002</strong>\nManifesta 4: European Biennial of Contemporary Art, various venues, Frankfurt, Germany, May 25 – August 25, 2002, curated by Iara Boubnova, Nuria Enguita Mayo, and Stéphanie Moisdon Trembley. Catalogue.\nVerso il futuro: Identità nell’arte italiana 1990–2002, Museo del Corso, Rome, Italy, June 26 – August 25, 2002, curated by Costantino D’Orazio and Ludovico Pratesi. Catalogue.\nExIt: Nuove geografie della creatività italiana, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, September 21, 2002 