, March 23 – May 21, 2006, curated by Gemma De Angelis Testa and Sergio Risaliti. ,Catalogue.\nVon Mäusen und Menschen / Of Mice and Men, 4th Berlin Biennale for Contemporary Art, various venues, Berlin, Germany, March 25 – June 5, 2006, curated by Maurizio Cattelan, Massimiliano ,Gioni, and Ali Subotnick. Catalogue.\nElettroshock: Il video in Italia dagli anni ‘70 a oggi (1973–2006), Central Academy of Fine Arts, ,Beijing and Guangdong Museum of Art, Guangzhou, China, March 25–26 and April 1–2, 2006, curated by Bruno Di Marino and Lara Nicoli. Catalogue.\nIl buco, Galleria Pio Monti, Rome, Italy, May 13–30, 2006, curated by Achille Bonito Oliva. ,Catalogue.\nIl Museo Insostenibile, La Rada, Locarno, Switzerland, April 8–9, 2006, curated by Noah Stolz.\nSupernova: Experience Pommery #3, Domaine Pommery, Reims, France, May 12 – October 31, ,2006, curated by Judicaël Lavrador. (A special issue of Beaux Arts Magazine was devoted to the ,exhibition.)\nYoung Italian Artists at the Turn of the Millennium, Galleria Continua, Beijing, China, July 1 – ,August 20, 2006. Catalogue.\nFrame: A Selection of Italian Artists, Gertrude Contemporary Art Spaces, Melbourne, Australia, August 25 – September 23, 2006, curated by Chiara Agnello and Roberta Tenconi. The exhibition was part of M.M.M. (milano.melbourne.milano), a cultural exchange project between the cities of Milan and Melbourne.\nA Secret Service: Art, Compulsion, Concealment, Hatton Gallery, Newcastle, UK, September 17 – November 11, 2006, a Hayward Gallery Touring Exhibition, curated by Richard Grayson. Catalogue.\n[Traveled to De La Warr Pavilion, Bexhill on Sea, UK, January 27 – April 15, 2007; Whitworth Art Gallery, Manchester, UK, May 5 – August 5, 2007.]\nCerealArt, NADA Art Fair, Miami, USA, December 6–10, 2006. Presentation of the works previously exhibited at The Wrong Gallery, New York, USA, in a 1:6 scale version. Cuoghi participated with a miniaturized version of F(IIA)l, 2005.\n\n<strong>2007</strong>\nOur Magic Hour: European artists’ show, Arario Gallery, Cheonan, South Korea, January 26 – March 11, 2007, curated by Milovan Farronato. Catalogue.\nI Want to Believe, Galerie Eva Presenhuber, Zurich, Switzerland, March 3 – April 7, 2007, curated by Milovan Farronato.\nDalla terra alla luna: Metafore di viaggio (parte I e II) / From the Earth to the Moon: Metaphors for Travel (Part I and II), Castello di Rivoli Museo d’Arte Contemporanea, Rivoli (Turin), Italy, April 4 – August 26, 2007, curated by Marcella Beccaria. Brochure.\nSequence 1: Pittura e scultura nella Collezione François Pinault / Sequence 1: Peinture et sculpture dans la Collection François Pinault, Palazzo Grassi, Venice, Italy, May 5 – November 11, 2007, curated by Alison M. Gingeras. Catalogue.\nOù? Scènes du Sud: Espagne, Italie, Portugal, Carré d’Art – Musée d’Art Contemporain de Nîmes, Nîmes, France, May 23 – September 23, 2007, curated by Françoise Cohen. Catalogue.\nSilenzio: Una mostra da ascoltare / Silence: Listen to the Show, Fondazione Sandretto Re Rebaudengo, Turin, Italy, June 1 – September 23, 2007, curated by Francesco Bonami. Catalogue.\nWho’s got the Big Picture?, M HKA – Museum voor Hedendaagse Kunst Antwerpen, Antwerp, Belgium, June 29 – November 18, 2007.\nItalian Mentalscapes: A Journey through Italian Contemporary Art, Tel Aviv Museum of Art, Tel Aviv, Israel, July 19 – October 6, 2007, curated by Demetrio Paparoni. Catalogue.\nFractured Figure: Works from the Dakis Joannou Collection, DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art, Athens, Greece, September 6, 2007– July 31, 2008, curated by Jeffrey Deitch. Catalogue.\nPlayback, ARC – Musée d’Art Moderne de la Ville de Paris, Paris, France, October 20, 2007 – January 6, 2008, curated by Anne Dressen. Catalogue.\n\n<strong>2008</strong>\nElectronic Lounge: La Donazione Halevim al Museo del Novecento, Aeroporto Malpensa, Terminal 1, Milan, Italy, February 27 – May 28, 2008, curated by Edoardo Gnemmi and Iolanda Ratti. Catalogue.\nL’Alchimia del