wer loaded with photographs of children interacting with the exhibited works. KINDERAMA was presented during the exhibition Skin Fruit at the New Museum in New York, USA, from March 3 to June 6, 2010.\n\n<strong>2011</strong>\nSolid Void, Progetto Diogene, Turin, Italy, November, 7–13, 2011. Workshop curated by Roberto Cuoghi and Gian Antonio Gilli.\n\n<strong>2013</strong>\nArimortis, Museo del Novecento, Milan, Italy, April 5 – September 8, 2013, group exhibition curated by Roberto Cuoghi and Milovan Farronato, in collaboration with DOCVA Documentation Center for Visual Arts. Catalogue.\n\n<strong>2015</strong>\nAmetria, Benaki Museum, Pireos St., Athens, Greece, June 12 – October 11, 2015, curated by Nicoletta De Rosa, Polina Kosmadaki, Alessandro Pasini, Tomaso Piantini, and Yorgos Tzirtzilakis. Group exhibition based on an idea by Roberto Cuoghi, organized by the DESTE Foundation for Contemporary Art in collaboration with the Benaki Museum.','Exhi & Bio','','inherit','closed','closed','','744-autosave-v1','','','2018-10-17 00:51:44','2018-10-16 22:51:44','',744,'http://localhost/robertocuoghi/?p=761',0,'revision','',0),(762,1,'2018-10-17 00:33:36','2018-10-16 22:33:36','Roberto Cuoghi (Modena, 1973). Lives and works in Milan, Italy\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h2>SOLO EXHIBITIONS</h2>\r\n<strong>1997</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi / Alberta Pellacani, Spazio Aperto, GAM – Galleria d’Arte Moderna di\r\nBologna, Bologna, Italy, December 19, 1997 – January 7, 1998, curated by Walter Guadagnini\r\nand Dede Auregli.\r\n\r\n<strong>2003</strong>\r\nRoberto Cuoghi: Foolish Things, Eldorado project room, GAMeC – Galleria d’Arte\r\nModerna e Contemporanea, Bergamo, Italy, February 9 – March 30, 2003, curated by\r\nGiacinto Di Pietrantonio and Alessandro Rabottini.\r\nRoberto Cuoghi, Galleria Massimo De Carlo, Milan, Italy, September 29 – October 30,\r\n2003.\r\n\r\n<strong>2005</strong>\r\nThe Wrong Gallery, New York, USA, March 7–30, 2005, curated by Maurizio Cattelan,\r\nMassimilian